Week 29 unfolds as a study in saturation rather than escalation. The pattern is not a single break with the past but a dense layering of moves that press on the same weak points of the system from many sides at once. Executive orders, redistricting schemes, detention contracts, university settlements, and data fights all arrive in the same span of days. Each one, taken alone, might look like a policy dispute or a hard\uc0\u8209 edged partisan maneuver. Together they describe a government learning to use every available lever\'97law, money, police, statistics, and memory\'97to favor those in power and sort everyone else into tiers of vulnerability. It is a week in which the machinery of the state does not lurch forward so much as settle more deeply into an authoritarian shape. That is the key shift.\
