On the Democracy Clock, this week begins and ends at 7:53 p.m. The underlying traits move: executive power without oversight, law as weapon, security forces aligned with regime interests, and stratified citizenship all grow more present and more entrenched. Yet the time does not advance because these shifts are not a sudden new phase; they are a consolidation of patterns already in motion. Courts still issue some checking rulings. Legislators still introduce voting\uc0\u8209 rights bills. Protesters still gather and, at times, force a response. The balance of power tilts further toward the executive and its allies, but not in a way that crosses a new structural threshold. The clock holds because what changes this week is density, not direction.\
