At the same time, the administration moves to reshape the very baseline of representation through the census. Donald Trump announces that he has instructed the Department of Commerce to design a new census that excludes undocumented immigrants from the count. The Constitution requires an enumeration of \'93whole persons,\'94 not citizens, and courts blocked related efforts in his first term. The new directive is thus both a legal challenge and a political signal. If carried out, it would shift House seats and federal funds away from states and districts with large immigrant populations, many of them urban and Democratic\uc0\u8209 leaning. Combined with the Texas and Indiana maps, the census plan shows how the regime is working on multiple layers of the same problem: who counts, who is counted, and who gets to draw the lines. Representation is being engineered from the ground up.\
